On January 1, 1863, President Abraham Lincoln issued the Emancipation Proclamation, ending slavery in states that rebelled against the Union. While it was not a perfect solution, it marked the beginning of the pursuit of perfection and the quest to realize the full promise of democracy in America. The proclamation inspired thousands of Americans and every Union victory became a sign of justice conquering injustice and freedom triumphing over bondage. On this New Year's Day, the article calls for unity and for the celebration of freedom as the sacred mission of the nation. It urges people to set aside differences and work towards creating a new birth of freedom in the United States in 2023.